Skinheads have never been given a a fair chance, from day one we have been crucified by todays society, the media, music companies and clubs. Skinheads, todays working class are crucified because of our beliefs, We show this by tattooing the picture of a skinhead being crucified on a cross. Since Our origin skinheads have been typically stereotyped as being NAZIS or Neo-NAZIS, yes some of us are Neo-NAZIS but we would prefer to be called White Beret or simply Skinheads.

The Movement began in England in the late 1960's, it became a fashion Statement among young white factory workers to shave their heads and because they were required to have their hair short anyway so that it didn't get caught in the machinery. When the racial, social and economical conditions Deteriorated, the immigrants began to over run the English Factories taking white jobs, thus it came time for us to retaliate, beating up any and all non-whites. The shaved heads are no longer a fashion statement, over time it has become a large part of our subculture, not only does it represent our very name of being a skinhead, but in a fight the advantage is already ours as we don't need to worry about having our hair pulled out.

Love and Hate go hand in hand, skinheads sometimes can be seen with love tattooed on the knuckles of their Left hand and hate on the Right. Put it like this, If you love your family then it is a natural instinct that you hate anyone that would attempt to threaten your family, so if you see it like that then Jews and blacks alike, the parasites of society are a direct threat to the white race over running us stealing our jobs it is expectable that we would hate something that makes threats to our existence. If the wish to stay in Israel or Africa then so be it, instead they wish to live in a white race controled land and try to take over what we have spent so long creating. It is ok to be black and Proud!!!, or Jewish and Proud, but the moment that you become white and Proud you are frowned upon as a Bigot, a NAZI, a Racist, a fascist or a skinhead.

Well these are a List of Sayings. " fifteen hundred years ago, Everybody knew the earth was the center of the universe, five hundred years ago, Everybody knew the earth was flat, and fifteen minutes ago you knew that people were alone on this planet. " " N-Y-P-D, means i will knock your punk ass Down!" "Every man dies, Not every man lives." "Every problem in this country is "race" related. Every problem, not just crime. These problems are rooted in the black community, the Hispanic community, the Asian... every non- Protestant group in our society. Look at the shit. Immigration... welfare... AIDS... they're all the problems of the non-white. Look at the statistics." "Eyes closed, we imagined our pain as a ball of white healing light floating around our feet and rising to our knees, our waist, our chest. Our chakras opening. The heart chakra. The head chakra. Chloe talked us into caves where we meet our power animal. Mine was a penguin." "I used to work in a funeral home to feel good about myself, just the fact that I was breathing." "If you find you're on your own, riding through green fields with the sun on your face, do not be afraid; for you're in Elysium and you're already dead!" "What we do in life echoes in eternity." "If you die in the wagons they feed you to the lions... The lions are worth more than we are. I think we are worth more than the zebras though. So they don't feed us to them. I'm not sure about the giraffe." "Your spoon does not bend because it is just that, a spoon. Mine bends because there is no spoon, just my mind. Link yourself to the spoon. Become the spoon and bend yourself." "My fellow Americans, a historic and unprecedented event has taken place. The question as to whether or not we are alone in the universe has been answered..." "The word has new meaning for all of us now. We are reminded not of our petty differences but of our common interests. Perhaps it's fate that today, July the Fourth, we will once again fight for our freedom. Not from tyranny, persecution or oppression. But from annihilation. We're fighting for our right to live, to exit. From this day on, the fourth day of July will no longer be remembered as an American holiday but as the day that all of mankind declared we will not go quietly into the night. We will not vanish without a fight. We will live on. We will survive."
